member.summary:
These settings are specific to a particular user. In normal mode: separate settings for each user account;
will roam to other machines if roaming is configured. In portable mode: always shared; user account and
machine name do not matter.

member.remarks:
This method checks if a file by the name (AppName).IsPortable.txt exists in the application path (see
). If that file exists, the settings are always stored in that application path.
This check is skipped if there is no entry assembly ( is null).
